thread.title: New York High-School Graduation Rates Rise

author: Leslie Brody
title: New York High-School Graduation Rates Rise
text:
Graduation rates for public high-school students across New York continued to inch up last year, according to state data released Wednesday.
New York’s statewide graduation rate in June edged up to 80.2% for the Class of 2017, up by half a percentage point from the prior year, and up more than 11 percentage points in a decade. New York City’s June graduation rate rose to 71.1%, up about 1 percentage point from the year before.
